The archaic production chain of hail probability fields generation

IRIS products
- IRIS generates echo top composites from single radar 45 dBZ and 50 dBZ TOPS products
  - CORECOMP   : 45 dBZ small composite
  - CORECOMP_L : 45 dBZ large composite
  - COREC50    : 50 dBZ small composite
  - COREC50_L  : 50 dBZ large composite

  These are in cartesian IRIS format, and are converted to PGM images.


Model data (same geometry and projection as IRIS composites)
- Two isotherm height model data fields, ZERO (0C) and M20 (-20C)
  are fetched from specific directory. These are text format and are converted
  to PGM images by extract_Tlevels_fromtext binary.


Combination

IRIS composites and model fields are inputs to tcsh script TOPSpipe.tcsh,
which combines those to POH (Probability Of Hail) and LHI (Large Hail Index)
PGM fields using algorithms coded by C.

Finally the POH and LHI fields are converted to cartesian IRIS data for IRIS use,
and converted to GIF images with background map by visualize_[POH,LHI]_data.tcsh
scripts.
